CNH Industrial's (CNHI) Note Issue Rated by Moody's - Analyst Blog


May 05, 2015, 06:49:00 PM EDT
By Zacks Equity Research, Zacks.com









































Shutterstock photo



Moody's Investors Service, a leading credit rating agency,
assigned provisional ratings to the notes to be issued by CNH
Equipment Trust 2015-B (CNH 2015-B), the debt issuing entity
of 
CNH Industrial N.V.
CNHI

, a premier global manufacturer in the capital goods sector. The
notes will be sponsored by CNH Industrial Capital America LLC, an
affiliate of CNH Industrial.
This CNH Equipment Trust 2014-B securitization involves
underlying collateral of U.S. retail installment contracts and
loans, backed by new or used agricultural equipment.
CNH Industrial's equipment lease securitization consists of five
tranches of A notes and one tranche of B notes. The Class A notes
have been assigned a rating of Aaa, which is awarded to securities
of the highest quality with the lowest level of credit risk.
In addition, its Class A-1 notes have received a P-1 rating,
indicating a superior ability to repay short-term debt obligations.
The Class B notes have been assigned an A2 rating, and are subject
to low credit risk.
The ratings of the notes address their credit quality and
signify the likelihood of the timely repayment of interest and the
ultimate payment of principal pursuant to their terms.
The strong ratings by Moody's reflect the first-rate quality of
the underlying collateral pool, the strength of the ABS structure,
and the experience and proficiency of the ABS servicer, New Holland
Credit Company, LLC.
In addition, there is an initial 4.50% hard credit enhancement
behind the Class A notes, consisting of a spread account and
subordination. Credit enhancements improve the credit quality and
ratings assigned to the notes. The subordination of the B tranche
provides a credit enhancement to the Class A notes of the
structure.
The notes could receive an upgrade in case the issuer provides
better credit protection to investors by way of enhancements.
Robust macroeconomic performance and improved agricultural markets,
being major drivers of performance of the collateral, might also
lead to an upgrade.
CNH Industrial presently holds a Zacks Rank #5 (Strong Sell).
Better-ranked stocks in the sector that look promising include
Daimler AG
DDAIF

, AB Volvo
VOLVY

and Cooper Tire & Rubber Co.
CTB

, each holding a Zacks Rank #2 (Buy).


